Well be working with NOAA weather data, which is downloaded using rnoaa::meteo_pull_monitors function in the code chunk below; similar code underlies the weather dataset used elsewhere in the course. Because this process can take some time, Ill cache the code chunk.

weather_df = 
  rnoaa::meteo_pull_monitors(
    c("USW00094728", "USW00022534", "USS0023B17S"),
    var = c("PRCP", "TMIN", "TMAX"), 
    date_min = "2021-01-01",
    date_max = "2022-12-31") |>
  mutate(
    name = recode(
      id, 
      USW00094728 = "CentralPark_NY", 
      USW00022534 = "Molokai_HI",
      USS0023B17S = "Waterhole_WA"),
    tmin = tmin / 10,
    tmax = tmax / 10) |>
  select(name, id, everything())

Same Plot From Last Time

weather_df |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = tmin, y = tmax, color = name)) +
  geom_point(alpha = .5) +
  labs(
    title = "Temperature Plot",
    x = "Min daily temp (Degrees Celsius)",
    y = "Max daily temp (Degrees Celsius)",
    color = "Location",
    caption = "Max vs. min daily temp in 3 locations; data from RNOAA"
  )

Adding Scales

weather_df |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = tmin, y = tmax, color = name)) +
  geom_point(alpha = .5) +
  labs(
    title = "Temperature Plot",
    x = "Min daily temp",
    y = "Max daily temp",
    color = "Location",
    caption = "Max vs. min daily temp in 3 locations; data from RNOAA"
  ) +
  scale_x_continuous(
    breaks = c(-15, 0, 15),
    labels = c("-15 C", "0", "15 C")
    ) +
  scale_y_continuous(
    position = "right",
    trans = "sqrt",
    limits = c(0, 30)
  )
## Warning in self$trans$transform(x): NaNs produced
## Warning: Transformation introduced infinite values in continuous y-axis
## Warning: Removed 302 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

Note that limits doesnt automatically update the scale/labeling on the corresponding axis, so might need to separately make adjustments to those after limiting.

Colors

weather_df |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = tmin, y = tmax, color = name)) +
  geom_point(alpha = .5) +
  labs(
    title = "Temperature Plot",
    x = "Min daily temp",
    y = "Max daily temp",
    color = "Location",
    caption = "Max vs. min daily temp in 3 locations; data from RNOAA"
  ) +
  scale_color_hue(h = c(150, 300))
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

Other option: viridis::scale_color_viridis(discrete = TRUE). The color schemes from the viridis package are better for color-blindness accessibility and clearer when printing in gray-scale. But, do need to specify discrete vs.continuous with functions from this package.

Themes

Used, for example, to move the location of the legend.

weather_df |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = tmin, y = tmax, color = name)) +
  geom_point(alpha = .5) +
  labs(
    title = "Temperature Plot",
    x = "Min daily temp",
    y = "Max daily temp",
    color = "Location",
    caption = "Max vs. min daily temp in 3 locations; data from RNOAA"
  ) +
  viridis::scale_color_viridis(discrete = TRUE) + 
  theme_bw() +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom")
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

theme_minimal() is another theme available.

Data Argument

Allows us to plot separate dataframes on top of one another. This can be useful when want to apply really different formatting to separate datasets within one plot.

ny_weather_df = 
  weather_df |> 
  filter(name == "CentralPark_NY")

hawaii_weather_df = 
  weather_df |> 
  filter(name == "Molokai_HI")

ggplot(ny_weather_df, aes(x = date, y = tmax)) +
  geom_point(aes(color = name)) +
  geom_line(data = hawaii_weather_df)

patchwork

weather_df |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = date, y = tmax, color = name)) +
  geom_point() +
  facet_grid(. ~ name)
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

ggp_temp_scatter = 
  weather_df |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = tmin, y = tmax, color = name)) +
  geom_point(alpha = .5)

ggp_prcp_density =
  weather_df |> 
  filter(prcp > 25) |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = prcp, fill = name)) +
  geom_density(alpha = .5) +
  theme(legend.position = "none")

ggp_tmax_date = 
  weather_df |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = date, y = tmax, color = name)) +
  geom_point() + 
  geom_smooth(se = FALSE) +
  theme(legend.position = "bottom")

ggp_temp_scatter + ggp_prcp_density
## Warning: Removed 17 rows containing missing values (`geom_point()`).

Data Manipulation

weather_df |> 
  mutate(
    name = fct_relevel(name, c("Molokai_HI", "CentralPark_NY", "Waterhole_WA"))
  ) |> 
  ggplot(aes(x = name, y = tmax)) +
  geom_boxplot()
